<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="popular-adj">popular <strong><em>adj</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'pɒpjələ(r)/    美 /'pɑːpjələr/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>流行的；受欢迎的</strong></h4>
<p>反 unpopular： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Online voting becomes <strong>increasingly popular</strong>, and many competitions get people involved in it.
在线投票越来越盛行，很多比赛都让人们参与进来投票。</p><footer>2016 江苏书面表达</footer></div>

<h3 id="be-popular-with-among">be popular with / among</h3>
<p>1.<strong>为…喜欢；受…欢迎：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The mobile phone is fashionable and convenient to carry, so it is very popular with youngsters.
这款手机样式新颖、携带方便，深受年轻人的欢迎。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Smart and pretty, Kate is very popular among her friends.
凯特既聪明又漂亮，深受朋友们的喜爱。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>公众的；大众化的；通俗的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a popular belief / opinion</strong>
普遍的观念/民意</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What we need most are popular science books.
我们最需要的是科普类图书。</p><footer>2014 浙江书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>in popular language 
用通俗的语言</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>This magazine is very popular <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ young people, who like its content and style.   （2007 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. with / among  </p></div>